<sect3 id="style-misc">
<title>Other settings for drawing</title>

<para>This small section has only two options.</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Menubar on the top of the screen in the style of
MacOS</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>This will turn on a menubar at the top of the screen.  This
menubar will reflect the menu options of the active
application.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry> 
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Apply fonts and colors to non-KDE apps</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>If this option is enabled, &kde; will try to force all
applications to use the &kde; colors and fonts.  This usually works, but
certain applications may behave oddly. </para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect3>

<sect3 id="style-toolbars">
<title>Style options for toolbars</title>
<para>This section of the panel is used for toolbars in &kde;
applications.</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Style options for toolbars</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>This option determines how toolbars will be displayed.  There
are 4 options: <guilabel>Icons only</guilabel>, <guilabel>Text only</guilabel>,
<guilabel>Text aside icons</guilabel>, and <guilabel>Text under
icons</guilabel>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Highlight buttons under mouse</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>When this option is enabled, any time you move the mouse
pointer over a button, the button will <quote>light up</quote>, to give
you feedback.  When disabled, the button does not change at
all.</para></listitem> 
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Toolbars are transparent when moving</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>If this option is enabled, toolbars will appear as a rectangle
while they are being moved.  If this option is disabled, the toolbar will
contain all graphic elements when being moved.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</sect3>

<sect3 id="style-effects">
<title>Effect options</title>

<para>Here you can set up some visual effects for menus, combo boxes,
and tooltips.</para>

<para>These are very processor and memory intensive, so you may wish to
disable some of them.</para>

<para>For menus, you can choose to have <guilabel>No menu
effect</guilabel>, or you can <guilabel>Fade menus</guilabel>,
where you will have menus fade on to your screen, or <guilabel>Animate
menus</guilabel>, which will give you menus that appear to slide out as
you click on them.</para>

<para>You can likewise animate combo boxes, by checking the box labelled
<guilabel>Animate combo boxes</guilabel></para>

<para>Tooltips are the small phrases that appear if you hover your mouse
button over an icon.  You can disable them here, by checking the
<guilabel>Disable tool tips</guilabel> checkbox.</para>

<para>If you like the tooltips, you might like them even more with some
visual effects.  You can choose between <guilabel>Plain tool
tips</guilabel>, <guilabel>Fade tool tips</guilabel> which appear to
fade onto your screen, or <guilabel>Rollout tool tips</guilabel>, where
the tooltips seem to unroll from under your mouse cursor.</para>

</sect3>
